    "en": {
      "title": "Pan Asia Bank MD Nimal Tillekeratne \u2018Banking CEO of the Year Sri Lanka 2022\u2019",
      "author": "Thilina Walpola",
      "body_lines": [
        "After taking Pan Asia Bank towards the pinnacle of the banking sector as The Truly Sri Lankan Bank, its CEO Nimal Tillekeratne has been awarded the prestigious \u2018Banking CEO of the Year Sri Lanka 2022\u2019 title by the esteemed Global Banking & Finance magazine. Within a short span of 5 years with Pan Asia Bank as Director/Chief Executive Officer since April 2017 and Managing Director since March 2021, he has taken the Bank on an exciting transformational journey on the strength of his 44 valuable years of experience in the banking industry in Sri Lanka and overseas. His quiet yet determined leadership has transformed Pan Asia Bank into an institution that has pioneered many firsts while carving a distinct identity as a Bank that values and nurtures its Sri Lankan identity.",
        "Leading the Bank through key milestones during his tenure include driving the Bank\u2019s digitalization journey while setting new benchmarks in green financing to promote renewable energy and support the SME sector.",
        "Providore unveils Concierge Service for senior citizens to order groceries via WhatsApp/text",
        "Melbourne\u2019s Firbank Grammar School partners with Ladies\u2019 College Colombo to offer VCE in Sri Lanka",
        "Leave a Reply Cancel replyYour email address will not be published. Required fields are marked *Comment Name *",
        "Save my name, email, and website in this browser for the next time I comment."
